@startuml
title GG Production Sequence - Configure, Build, Package, Deploy, Serve

actor "Owner / Buyer" as Owner
participant "GG Console\n(Control Plane)" as Console
participant "Config + Registry\nprofile/routes/surfaces/copy" as Config
participant "Blogger API v3\nRoot CMS" as RootCMS
participant "Blogger API v3\nStore CMS" as StoreCMS
participant "Build System" as Build
participant "Checks / Doctor" as Checks
participant "Production Optimizer" as Optimizer
participant "Release Packager" as Packager
participant "Cloudflare Deploy" as Cloudflare
participant "Blogger Theme" as BloggerTheme
participant "Browser / Visitor" as Visitor

== CMS and profile configuration ==
Owner -> Console: Open GG Console
Console -> Config: Read active profile, routes, surfaces, flags
Console -> Owner: Show project health and setup status

Owner -> Console: Connect Google account
Console -> RootCMS: List available Blogger blogs
RootCMS --> Console: Blogs, blogIds, URLs, counts
Console -> StoreCMS: List available Blogger blogs
StoreCMS --> Console: Blogs, blogIds, URLs, counts

Owner -> Console: Select Root CMS and Store CMS
Console -> Config: Write cms.root and cms.store config
Console -> Config: Write source boundary and canonical mapping
Console -> Checks: Validate source boundary
Checks --> Console: Root/store CMS status

== Production build ==
Owner -> Console: Run Doctor
Console -> Checks: Validate config, registry, routes, copy, a11y, outputs
Checks -> Config: Read expected contracts
Checks --> Console: PASS / warnings / blockers

alt Doctor blocked
  Console -> Owner: Show blocking issue and next action
else Doctor passed
  Owner -> Console: Run Build
  Console -> Build: Build production artifacts from source
  Build -> Config: Resolve profile, routes, surfaces, registry
  Build -> RootCMS: Optional read-only source inspection
  Build -> StoreCMS: Optional read-only product source inspection
  Build --> Console: Build artifacts ready
end

== Optimization and packaging ==
Console -> Optimizer: Optimize production output
Optimizer -> Optimizer: Minify JS/CSS/HTML where safe
Optimizer -> Optimizer: Preserve Blogger XML safety
Optimizer -> Optimizer: Generate private source maps if enabled
Optimizer -> Optimizer: Exclude public .map files by default
Optimizer --> Console: Optimized dist ready

Owner -> Console: Package release
Console -> Packager: Create release manifest, checksums, buyer package
Packager -> Checks: Validate clean package
Checks --> Packager: PASS / FAIL

alt Package validation fails
  Packager --> Console: Packaging failure with path/contract issue
  Console -> Owner: Show failure and required fix
else Package validation passes
  Packager --> Console: Release package ready
  Console -> Owner: Show release artifact and deploy readiness
end

== Deployment ==
Owner -> Console: Deploy approved artifact
Console -> Cloudflare: Deploy static surfaces, assets, worker, headers
Cloudflare --> Console: Deployment result

Owner -> BloggerTheme: Upload/update Blogger root template if required
BloggerTheme --> Owner: Blogger theme active

== Runtime serving ==
Visitor -> Cloudflare: Request /landing or /store or assets
Cloudflare --> Visitor: Static surface / worker-governed response

Visitor -> Cloudflare: Request /
Cloudflare -> BloggerTheme: Route to Blogger-owned root/blog surface
BloggerTheme --> Visitor: Crawlable Blogger SSR HTML

Visitor -> Cloudflare: Request /store/
Cloudflare --> Visitor: Static Yellow Cart canonical store surface

Visitor -> Visitor: JS progressively enhances UI
Visitor -> Visitor: Primary content remains meaningful without JS

@enduml
